Source: icinga-web
Section: php
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Markus Frosch <markus.frosch@netways.de>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.50~), autotools-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.1
Homepage: http://www.icinga.org
#Vcs-Git: git://git.debian.org/collab-maint/icinga-web.git
#Vcs-Browser: http://git.debian.org/?p=collab-maint/icinga-web.git;a=summary

Package: icinga-web
Architecture: all
Depends: icinga (>= 1.6.1), ucf, dbconfig-common, php5-cli, php5, php5-gd, php5-xsl, php5-mysql, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: mysql-client
Description: Icinga offers 2 web interfaces for users to view Icinga
 monitoring results and send commands to the Icinga Core. In both Icinga
 New and Classic Web, host and service status, history, notifications
 and status maps are available to keep a check on the health of your
 network in real-time. Both also support IPv4 as well as IPv6 addresses.

Package: icinga-web-plugin-pnp
Architecture: all
Depends: icinga-web (= ${source:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: This is only an adapter to integrate pnp graphs to your
 icinga-web interface, you must install pnp4nagios separately. After
 successful installation you should see a new icon in your host and
 services overview which display the pnp graphs for the host/service 
 when being clicked upon.

